@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
    ViewBag.Title = "Filters & Valves – Drip Smart USA";
    ViewBag.MetaDescription = "DripSmart filtration and control products — screen filters, disc filters, sand media filters, pressure regulators, and control valves for drip irrigation systems.";
}

<section class="page-hero" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #181F4E 0%, #1e2d6e 100%);">
    <div class="container page-hero-inner">
        <div class="page-hero-text">
            <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/products">Products</a> / <span>Filters & Valves</span></nav>
            <h1>Filters, Valves & Pressure Management</h1>
            <p>Clean water and controlled pressure are the difference between a drip system that lasts two decades and one that clogs in its first season. DripSmart filtration products protect your investment from day one.</p>
            <a href="/find-a-dealer" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:24px;">Talk to a Dealer</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Why Filtration Matters -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="align-items:center;">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">The Foundation</span>
                <h2>Bad Filtration Kills Good Drip Systems</h2>
                <p>Drip emitters have tiny flow paths — typically 0.5–2mm. Even fine particles, algae, or mineral precipitation can clog them. A properly sized and maintained filtration system is not optional; it's the most critical component in the head works.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:14px;">DripSmart filtration products are sized for your water source, flow rate, and emitter type — whether you're drawing from a clean municipal supply, a surface canal, a pond, or a reclaimed water source.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="benefit-stat-card" style="align-self:start;">
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">0.5mm</span><span class="big-label">Typical emitter flow path diameter</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">#1</span><span class="big-label">Cause of drip system failure: clogging</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">20yr</span><span class="big-label">System life with proper filtration</span></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Filter Types -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--blue-pale);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Filtration Products</span>
            <h2>Matched to Your Water Quality</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid" style="margin-top:40px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="settings"></i></div>
                <h3>Screen Filters</h3>
                <p>Inline wye-type or T-type screen filters for clean water sources with light sediment loads. Available in 3/4" through 3" sizes with 80-, 120-, and 200-mesh screens. Simple manual cleaning or auto-flush options.</p>
                <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:12px;"><strong>Best for:</strong> Municipal water, well water with low sand load</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="disc"></i></div>
                <h3>Disc Filters</h3>
                <p>Stacked grooved discs provide three-dimensional filtration — capturing particles, algae, and fibrous matter that bypass screen filters. Self-flushing models flush automatically at a set pressure differential.</p>
                <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:12px;"><strong>Best for:</strong> Pond, canal, and surface water with organic matter</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="cylinder"></i></div>
                <h3>Sand Media Filters</h3>
                <p>Tanks filled with graded silica sand provide the highest level of filtration — essential for surface water, recycled water, and sources with heavy biological or sediment loads. Multiple tank configurations for high flow rates.</p>
                <p style="font-size:0.82rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:12px;"><strong>Best for:</strong> Surface water, reclaimed water, high-sediment wells</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Valves & Pressure -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Control & Regulation</span>
            <h2>Valves & Pressure Management</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="margin-top:40px; gap:24px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="sliders"></i></div>
                <h3>Pressure Regulators</h3>
                <p>Maintain consistent downstream pressure regardless of supply variation. Critical for PC emitter performance and long lateral runs. Available in preset and adjustable models from 6–30 PSI.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="droplets"></i></div>
                <h3>Air Release & Vacuum Relief Valves</h3>
                <p>Prevent air locks during filling and vacuum damage during shutdown. Installed at system high points and lateral ends to protect emitters from siphon backflow and air-induced clogging.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="droplets"></i></div>
                <h3>Flush Valves & End Caps</h3>
                <p>Automatic flush valves open at low pressure during system startup and shutdown — flushing accumulated sediment from lateral ends before emitters are pressurized.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="settings-2"></i></div>
                <h3>Solenoid Control Valves</h3>
                <p>Electric solenoid valves for zone control — compatible with DripSphere OS™ controllers and standard 24VAC irrigation controllers. Available in 1" through 4" sizes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--midnight); color:white;">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <h2 style="color:white;">Proper Filtration Is a System Design Decision</h2>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75); max-width:540px; margin:16px auto 0;">Filter sizing depends on your flow rate, water quality, and emitter type. Your certified DripSmart dealer will design the right head works for your specific water source.</p>
        <a href="/find-a-dealer" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px; display:inline-block;">Find a Local Dealer</a>
    </div>
</section>
